docs.abstract: As the primary approaches, Franklin Graham brings Jesus — and a conservative political message — to a state with a vast pool of evangelical voters.
docs.snippet: As the primary approaches, Franklin Graham brings Jesus — and a conservative political message — to a state with a vast pool of evangelical voters.
docs.lead_paragraph: PASADENA, Calif. — Franklin Graham stood in a packed locker room at the Rose Bowl, surrounded by fellow evangelists, pastors, and his top Los Angeles donors. It was two weeks before the California primary, and Mr. Graham was urging them to take a stand against their state’s “blue wall.”

headline.main: The Evangelical Fight to Win Back California
headline.print_headline: An Evangelical  Fights to Make California Red

docs.abstract: The annual event has become a hub of influence-peddling, as foreign dignitaries, religious leaders and lobbyists jockey for access to top American officials.
docs.snippet: The annual event has become a hub of influence-peddling, as foreign dignitaries, religious leaders and lobbyists jockey for access to top American officials.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — With a lineup of prayer meetings, humanitarian forums and religious panels, the National Prayer Breakfast has long brought together people from all over the world for an agenda built around the teachings of Jesus.

headline.main: At Prayer Breakfast, Guests Seek Access to a Different Higher Power
headline.print_headline: Gathering for Faith, Unity and a Lot of Influence

byline.original: By Kenneth P. Vogel and Elizabeth Dias

docs.abstract: The refusal by Senate Republicans to act on President Obama’s nomination of Merrick Garland to the Supreme Court, paving the way for Justice Gorsuch, reverberated powerfully after Tuesday’s rulings.
docs.snippet: The refusal by Senate Republicans to act on President Obama’s nomination of Merrick Garland to the Supreme Court, paving the way for Justice Gorsuch, reverberated powerfully after Tuesday’s rulings.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The consequences of President Trump’s nomination of Neil M. Gorsuch to the Supreme Court — and the Republican blockade of President Barack Obama’s nomination of Merrick B. Garland in 2016 for that seat — became powerfully clear on Tuesday after the court’s conservative majority handed down major decisions to uphold Mr. Trump’s travel ban and in favor of abortion rights opponents.

headline.main: Abortion and Travel Ban Rulings Are Victory for G.O.P. Tactics on Gorsuch
headline.print_headline: G.O.P. Tactics in 2016 Pay Off in Gorsuch, Who Proves Decisive Figure

byline.original: By Elizabeth Dias and Sydney Ember

docs.abstract: The Mormon Women for Ethical Government called for a suspension of Judge Kavanaugh’s confirmation proceedings, pending a thorough investigation.
docs.snippet: The Mormon Women for Ethical Government called for a suspension of Judge Kavanaugh’s confirmation proceedings, pending a thorough investigation.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As turmoil grows over sexual misconduct allegations against Judge Brett M. Kavanaugh, casting doubts over his confirmation to the Supreme Court, a group of Mormon women is calling on senators to suspend his confirmation proceedings until a thorough investigation is completed.

headline.main: Mormon Women’s Group Seeks Inquiry Into Kavanaugh Allegations
headline.print_headline: A Mormon Women’s Group Seeks a Break in the Process

docs.abstract: Scheduling fights in the Senate. Student evaluations. Here’s a distilled version of what has happened since President Trump introduced his court nominee to the world.
docs.snippet: Scheduling fights in the Senate. Student evaluations. Here’s a distilled version of what has happened since President Trump introduced his court nominee to the world.
docs.lead_paragraph: It may seem like a month ago, but it hasn’t even been two weeks since President Trump nominated Judge Brett M. Kavanaugh to the Supreme Court. And amid the noise of this especially frenetic news cycle, you may worry you’ve missed out on a new development.

headline.main: A Cheat Sheet to Catch Up on the Supreme Court Nomination

docs.abstract: Ms. Kelly easily won the Democratic nomination but faces a tough race in the fall. In a key House district, Chris Pappas defeated a newcomer to the state, Maura Sullivan.
docs.snippet: Ms. Kelly easily won the Democratic nomination but faces a tough race in the fall. In a key House district, Chris Pappas defeated a newcomer to the state, Maura Sullivan.
docs.lead_paragraph: PORTSMOUTH, N.H. — Democratic voters in New Hampshire selected Molly Kelly, a former state senator, as their nominee for governor on Tuesday, as female candidates for governorships continue to show their strength in primary elections this year.

headline.main: Molly Kelly Wins in New Hampshire and Will Face Sununu for Governor’s Seat
headline.print_headline: Women’s Wave Sweeps Through Primary for New Hampshire Governor

docs.abstract: Tribes think they may be able to increase turnout in the face of a strict voter ID law. But it will be a challenge.
docs.snippet: Tribes think they may be able to increase turnout in the face of a strict voter ID law. But it will be a challenge.
docs.lead_paragraph: FORT YATES, N.D. — Nobody in the squat yellow house serving as the Standing Rock Sioux Tribe’s get-out-the-vote headquarters knew its address.

headline.main: In North Dakota, Native Americans Try to Turn an ID Law to Their Advantage
headline.print_headline: In North Dakota, Native Americans Try to Turn ID Law Into a Gain

docs.abstract: Michael Bloomberg, the former mayor of New York, acknowledged he has some differences with progressive Democrats, but said, “It’s impossible to conceive that I could run as a Republican.”
docs.snippet: Michael Bloomberg, the former mayor of New York, acknowledged he has some differences with progressive Democrats, but said, “It’s impossible to conceive that I could run as a Republican.”
docs.lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — Michael R. Bloomberg is actively considering a campaign for president as a Democrat in 2020, concluding that it would be his only path to the White House even as he voices stark disagreements with progressives on defining issues including bank regulation, stop-and-frisk police tactics and the #MeToo movement.

headline.main: Bloomberg May Run for President as a Democrat. Some of His Views May Cause Him Trouble.
headline.print_headline: Bloomberg Weighs 2020 Run Cast as a Discordant Democrat

byline.original: By Alexander Burns and Sydney Ember

docs.abstract: As a college student, more than a quarter-century ago, Ms. Abrams joined in the burning of the state flag, which at the time was viewed by many as a lingering symbol of white supremacy.
docs.snippet: As a college student, more than a quarter-century ago, Ms. Abrams joined in the burning of the state flag, which at the time was viewed by many as a lingering symbol of white supremacy.
docs.lead_paragraph: ATLANTA — At a protest on the steps of the Georgia Capitol in 1992, Stacey Abrams, now the Democratic candidate for governor, joined in the burning of the state flag, which at the time incorporated the Confederate battle flag design and was viewed by many as a lingering symbol of white supremacy.

headline.main: Stacey Abrams’s Burning of Georgia Flag With Confederate Symbol Surfaces on Eve of Debate
headline.print_headline: Abrams Role In Burning Georgia Flag Resurfaces

docs.abstract: Mr. Jones, a Holocaust denier and former member of the American Nazi Party, was the sole Republican candidate in a suburban Chicago congressional district.
docs.snippet: Mr. Jones, a Holocaust denier and former member of the American Nazi Party, was the sole Republican candidate in a suburban Chicago congressional district.
docs.lead_paragraph: Arthur Jones, a Holocaust denier described as a Nazi by the Illinois Republican Party, won the Republican primary on Tuesday in the state’s Third Congressional District, a heavily Democratic district that includes part of Chicago and its suburbs, according to The Associated Press.

headline.main: Denounced by His Party as a Nazi, Arthur Jones Wins Illinois G.O.P. Congressional Primary
